  note for FormSchema "FormSchema&lt;T&gt; is generic over the value type.\nWhen T is supplied (e.g. CreateUserCommand),\nfield keys are constrained to keyof T &amp; string —\ntypos are COMPILE errors. Default permissive\nfor legacy callers."
  note for SchemaField "Discriminated union — each variant declares\nONLY the props that make sense for its type.\nA text field can no longer carry options /\nmask / currency at compile time."
  note for SchemaWhenPredicate "Pure predicate evaluated on every form-state\ntick. Returning false REMOVES the control\nfrom the FormGroup until it flips back —\nso hidden required fields don't block submit."
  note for CrossFieldRule "FormGroup-level validator. Runs on every\nvalue change, registers errors keyed by\n'xfield:&lt;rule.id&gt;' on each targeted control,\nso the field-level error renderer surfaces them."
  note for SchemaFormSectionEvent "tab:change is the canonical event.\nsection:tab-change is preserved for back-\ncompat — both fire on tab navigation\nuntil the legacy name is removed."
